conversations.user: When is the scholarship application deadline?

conversations.user: Where do I claim my ID?

conversations.user: Do students need to wear a uniform?
conversations.bot: Yes, wearing a school uniform is mandatory for all students during class hours.

conversations.user: Where can I buy the school uniform?
conversations.bot: You can purchase the official school uniform at the campus cooperative store or partner suppliers.

conversations.user: What if my uniform is not ready yet?
conversations.bot: Students may wear appropriate civilian attire during the first two weeks of classes while waiting for their uniforms.

conversations.user: Are there dormitories available on campus?
conversations.bot: Yes, we offer on-campus dormitories for both male and female students. Rooms are available on a first-come, first-served basis.

conversations.user: How do I apply for a dormitory room?
conversations.bot: You can apply by visiting the student affairs office and filling out the dormitory application form.

conversations.user: How much is the dormitory fee per semester?
conversations.bot: The dormitory fee ranges from ₱3,000 to ₱5,000 per semester depending on the room type.

conversations.user: When will the class schedules be released?
conversations.bot: Class schedules are usually released a week before the start of the semester. Please check your student portal for updates.

conversations.user: Can I request to change my class schedule?
conversations.bot: Yes, schedule adjustments are allowed during the first week of classes. Visit your department office for assistance.

conversations.user: Where can I find my complete class schedule?
conversations.bot: Log in to the student portal and go to the 'My Schedule' section to view your class schedule.
